text: Curious info from David Paulides. Most male corpses found in water are face-down, while most female corpses in water end up face-up. The big exception is mysterious disappearances of young men in cities, whose cadavers are found upstream from where last seen - always face-up.

Old stadiums are a surprisingly nice to take a walk around when they're empty. Moss, broken concrete, wild-ish grass underneath. All that excitement that has taken place leaves a trace in the air. You can sense it even in the cool morning air.

Tree roots are actually not as large as the rest of the tree, as urban legends tell. Even in ideal conditions, and on large trees, they never grow further than 6 meters deep. Trees in cities most often are unable to reach their optimal root depth and remain shallow. Curious.
Continue with this train of thought and you reach Borges' "Pierre Menard, Author of the Quixote"
Nothing in our world will change before we change the ruleset of chess. Fischer understood this, and so did Borges. Culture is downstream from chess.

God used red dirt for the creation of Adam. Even though Genesis omits this, the Hebrew word for "brown red" is Adom. All other creation stories similar to the one in Genesis mention the earth from which he was made to be red. The ground's colour in Palestina is also red.
Ofc this is not canonic obviously, take it with a grain of salt. And there must be a reason the colour is not mentioned in the Bible

As we look at Eden more, we start to notice the second tree, the one of Life. But it plays no role in the story - its fruit remains hanging there, no one bothers to pick and eat them. There is no ban on it, no one prevents Adam and Eve to eat it and attain eternal life, and yet..

they never bother to taste it. They do not even notice it, and often neither do the people reading Genesis. Does this seem weird to us? We do the same, every day eating from the forbidden tree, and always forgetting about the tree of eternal life's very existence. Very ironic

Some say trees' leaves did not fall off in the Garden of Eden.. others claim Adam and Eve could hear God's footsteps in the crunch of leaves on the ground, which means the Fall happened in autumn (or "fall" in American English hehe). Curious symbolism, Nature reflects metaphysics

There are no atheists in the foxholes, but the opposite is also true: there are no atheists on the mountaintop, there is no atheism in the triumphant chariot of the victor. Atheisms exists only in the middle. In the mediocrity. Be hot or be cold, but be not lukewarm.

It is wrong that we turn to faith only at our weakest and fear-filled moments. We also feel God at our highest, when our lust for life overflows, when the entire world seems to cower at our feet. When everything else is below you, God can be seen above.
